The 29-year-old man accused of kidnapping and murdering Durban North woman, now faces 16 charges. He appeared briefly in the Durban Magistrateâ€™s Court on Friday and again on Tuesday. The charges he faces includes rape, murder, kidnapping and crimen injuria, among others. The Assagay resident is being detained at the Durban North SAPS holding cells. A formal bail hearing is expected to take place early in March but the state says it will oppose bail. Lee went missing from Durban North in early January, her charred body was found on a New Hanover farm in the KwaZulu-Natal Midlands two days after she disappeared. Since then an online petition was established calling for her murderer to be brought to book. The petition has over 3000 supporters so far.